name: SUPER FAMICOM
description:
Super Famicom is a 16-bit video game console developed by Nintendo that was released in 1990 in Japan, 1991 in the United States, 1992 in Europe and Australasia (Oceania) and South America in 1993.
In Japan, the system was called Super Famicom or SFC and was released with just two games: Super Mario World and F-Zero
